{"id":43,"date":"2025-03-27T11:10:06","date_gmt":"2025-03-27T11:10:06","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/?p=43"},"modified":"2025-03-27T11:10:14","modified_gmt":"2025-03-27T11:10:14","slug":"classic-fresh-fruit-tart","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/2025\/03\/27\/classic-fresh-fruit-tart\/","title":{"rendered":"Classic Fresh Fruit Tart"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>This elegant tart features a buttery crust, creamy custard filling, and vibrant fresh fruits.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Ingredients<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>For the Crust<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>1 \u00bc cups all-purpose flour<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bd cup unsalted butter (cold, cubed)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bc cup powdered sugar<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 egg yolk<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 tbsp ice water<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>For the Custard Filling<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>2 cups whole milk<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bd cup granulated sugar<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>4 egg yolks<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bc cup cornstarch<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp vanilla extract<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 tbsp unsalted butter<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>For the Topping<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>1 cup strawberries (sliced)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bd cup blueberries<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bd cup kiwi (sliced)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bd cup raspberries<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bc cup apricot jam (for glaze)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Instructions<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 1: Making the Tart Crust<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>In a food processor, combine flour, butter, and powdered sugar. Pulse until crumbly.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add egg yolk and ice water. Pulse until dough forms.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shape into a disc, wrap in plastic, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Roll out dough and press into a 9-inch tart pan.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Prick the bottom with a fork and chill for another 10 minutes.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Preheat oven to 375\u00b0F (190\u00b0C). Line the crust with parchment paper and pie weights.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bake for 15 minutes, remove weights, and bake for another 10 minutes. Cool completely.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 2: Making the Custard<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>In a saucepan, heat milk over medium heat until steaming (do not boil).<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>In a bowl, whisk egg yolks, sugar, and cornstarch until smooth.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Gradually add hot milk, whisking constantly.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Return mixture to saucepan and cook until thickened.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Remove from heat, add vanilla and butter, stirring until smooth.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cool slightly, then spread evenly into the tart shell.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 3: Decorating the Tart<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Arrange sliced fruits on top of the custard in an artistic pattern.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Warm apricot jam and brush over the fruits for a glossy finish.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 4: Serving<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Chill for at least 1 hour before slicing.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Serve fresh and enjoy!<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>This elegant tart features a buttery crust, creamy custard filling, and vibrant fresh fruits. Ingredients For the Crust For the Custard Filling For the Topping [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":44,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[4],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-43","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-desserts"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/43","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=43"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/43\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":45,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/43\/revisions\/45"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/44"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=43"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=43"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=43"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}